^ is there an equivalent command in &name to the &name 'deltree " command ? 
</text_embedded>
<text_normal> 

^ " rm &char /foo / bar " : remove /foo / bar and all its contents and subdirectories 
^ " rm -rf /foo / bar " : as above , but delete read-only files without asking fi rst 
^ 'man rm " or " info fileutils " for more details . 
</text_normal>
</message_body>
